content: I was having issues with crashing when starting a session but an uninstall/reinstall fixed that. The latest features are excellent. I've been using the app for years and it's been well worth the price. I really appreciate the work Cdr. Divine and his team have put in up to now. Keep it up legends üôèüå¨Ô∏èüí™

2/1/21 This latest update is horrible. The music is so depressing and the transitions are so blunt and disjointed. I can't meditate with this new version. ------------- Great app, it really has helped me with my breath. At first, I thought it was a bit hokey but with time and practice, it really was powerful. I wish, however, that there was the ability to add more than a single reminder notification each day.
It keeps crashing each time I click start practice button. I liked the old version better as it consistently worked.
Great App. Especially when used with the Unbeatable Challenge!
Why does the sound abruptly stop and start. Not calming and incredibly hard to keep focus
I haven't been able to open the app!
Application crashes 100% of the time on Pixel 4.
Great app love using it every day

Tried an uninstalled after the first session. The most important thing for such an app is to have sound that guides you. Here, whatever the level, the music is cut abruptly between each breathe-in / hold / breathe-out. It disturbs the calmness which is one of the main objectives
Fabulous addition to the unbeatable mind course. Epic. Life transforming.
Excellent App for an Unbeatable Mind
Appreciate the emphasis on consistency 1st.
Super helpful app to guide box breathing and develop breath awareness. We've started using this app to ooen our meetings.
Get this! Comprehensive, well compiled tool for awareness and breath practice.
The voice prompts were the one thing that set this app apart,now it's just confusing music

Initially i loved it but now after the latest update it's horrible. Music crashes at times and terrible clicking sound in between steps. So annoying! Or maybe it's developers idea on how to make practise more difficult so that practioners grow more meditative muscles? Nope, dont think so. If its not fixed i'll probably look for something different.
The app freezes from the beginning on my S9+ so I was never able to use it :(

I have found this app unuseable due to a fuzzy clicking sound at the change 
of breath ie. every 4 seconds. For those old enough to remember, it's like 
the sound you get on a cassette tape or poorly ripped compilation cd when 
it jumps from one track to the next. Very irritating to listen to when 
you're trying to relax!!

Have improved my breathing through my nose and breath control during 
running tremendously. Love the belt goals too!
Fantastic app! I high recommend it!
